Colonial Secretary Office
25th November 1871

Sir,
I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your letter of yesterday's date, notifying your intended departure from the Colony and your loving Mr. T.J. Hildridge in charge of the United States Consulate, and to inform you that His Excellency the Governor in Chief has been pleased to approve of the arrangement.

I have the honor to be
Sir
Your most obdt Servant
<unclear> Reg </unclear> <unclear/>
Acting Colonial Secretary

William Hogan Esq
U.S. Consular Agent

